N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 56.16 - Imposition of costs against complainant or respondent

State Regulations

The board may, in its discretion, impose costs against either
complainant or respondent, in such amount as will reimburse the board for any
expenses incurred by it in connection with a hearing, depending on the final
outcome or disposition thereof. Notes
